text.tspan: Literacy rates vs. average years of schooling, 1970 to 2010
The vertical axis measures literacy rates for population aged 15 and older, combining data from a number of sources
(see sources tab for more details). The horizontal axis measures average number of years of total schooling across
all education levels, for the population aged 15-64.
Adult literacy rate, population 15+ years, both sexes (%)
Source: Literacy rates (World Bank, CIA World Factbook, and other sources), Lee and Lee (2016)
